        Industry <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Parcel distribution:</strong> ARB is widely deployed in parcel carrier sort centers (UPS, FedEx, DHL, national post services). The technology handles the enormous variety of parcel sizes, shapes, and weights that flow through distribution hubs. ARB singulation converts randomly loaded induction streams into scannable single-file flows. ARB diverting routes packages to destination chutes at rates exceeding 60 packages per minute per divert point.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">E-commerce fulfillment:</strong> E-commerce warehouses use ARB to sort outbound orders to shipping lanes by carrier, service level, or geographic zone. The mix of polybags, padded mailers, small boxes, and large cases that characterizes e-commerce order streams suits ARB's ability to handle diverse product sizes without adjustment.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Food and beverage packaging:</strong> ARB conveyors sort cases of food and beverage products to palletizing lanes by SKU, flavor, or size. The gentle divert action prevents case damage that mechanical pushers cause. <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Food-grade</a> ARB belt materials meet FDA requirements for incidental contact.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Retail distribution:</strong> Retail distribution centers use ARB to sort cases and cartons to store-specific lanes. A single ARB sorter replaces multiple mechanical diverters along a trunk line, reducing equipment count, maintenance, and floor space.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Airport baggage handling:</strong> Airport baggage systems use ARB for bag sorting and diverting to makeup carousels. The gentle handling reduces bag damage claims. The no-gap capability handles the dense bag flows that occur during peak travel periods.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
